Armed Constabulary
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Hist. Also lower case initials. [nf W3.] The armed police, reconstituted as a civilian force after 1886, formed in 1867 under the Armed Constabulary Ordinance as the first national police force (?called earlier the armed police force) orig. to combat hostile Maoris, and to keep civil order, until the civil (unarmed) police was established in 1886 under the Police Force Act.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:A.C.
